ors by typically 0.2-0.4 dex.\nNuclear level densities tend to affect abundance predictions mainly in the\nZ=74-79 regions. The uncertainties associated with the neutron-producing\nreaction 13C(a,n)16O and the unknown beta-decay rates are found to have a low\nimpact on the overall surface enrichment\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Sep 2021 12:29:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-27"}
