 loading, enabling monitoring of the loading itself and the spatial\nuniformity of the Gd concentration over the 35 days it took to reach the top of\nthe detector. During the subsequent commissioning the recirculation rate was\nincreased to 120 m$^3$/h, resulting in a constant and uniform distribution of\nGd throughout the detector and water transparency equivalent to that of\nprevious pure-water operation periods. Using an Am-Be neutron calibration\nsource the mean neutron capture time was measured to be $115\\pm1$ $\\mu$s, which\ncorresponds to a Gd concentration of $111\\pm2$ ppm, as expected for this level\nof Gd loading. This paper describes changes made to the water circulation\nsystem for this detector upgrade, the Gd loading procedure, detector\ncommissioning, and the first neutron calibration measurements in SK-Gd.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Sep 2021 12:47:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 4 Sep 2021 07:49:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 15 Dec 2021 15:50:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-27"}
